What's in a day?
Every day is a special day for someone, somewhere. For example, your birthday is just another ordinary
day for the rest of the world, but for you, it is a very special, and important day. Similarly, some days are special, and have great significance not only for individuals, but for the whole world.
We are talking about some such days, here. Many of these days of international observance have been established by the United Nations, or its agencies.
This issue of Tell Me Why presents our world's important days of observance for international awareness.
